===Etymology 1===
Sense of sleeping berth possibly from Scottish English {{term|bunker||seat, bench|lang=en}}, origin is uncertain but possibly Scandinavian.
Confer Old Swedish {{term|bunke||boards used to protect the cargo of a ship|lang=gmq-osw}}.
See also {{term|boarding|lang=en}}, {{term|flooring|lang=en}} and confer {{term|bunch|lang=en}}.

